["1. **Replace `javax.enterprise` import statement with `jakarta.enterprise`:**\n\n   Java EE and Jakarta EE namespaces are different. Java EE uses `javax` namespace while Jakarta EE uses `jakarta` namespace. Quarkus is based on Jakarta EE, so we need to replace the `javax.enterprise` import statement with `jakarta.enterprise`.\n\n   The line `import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;` needs to be changed to `import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;`.\n\n2. **Replace `java.io.Serializable` import statement:**\n\n   `java.io.Serializable` is not required in Quarkus as it uses a different mechanism for dependency injection and serialization.\n\n   The line `import java.io.Serializable;` can be safely removed.\n\n3. **Update `pom.xml` dependencies:**\n\n   Quarkus uses different dependencies than Java EE. We need to update the `pom.xml` file to include Quarkus dependencies.\n\n   Add the following dependencies to the `pom.xml` file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <dependency>\n       <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n       <artifactId>quarkus-agroal</artifactId>\n   </dependency>\n   <dependency>\n       <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n       <artifactId>quarkus-jdbc-postgresql</artifactId>\n   </dependency>\n   <dependency>\n       <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n       <artifactId>quarkus-resteasy-jsonb</artifactId>\n   </dependency>\n   <dependency>\n       <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n       <artifactId>quarkus-arc</artifactId>\n   </dependency>\n   ```\n\n   These dependencies include the necessary components for database connectivity, JSON serialization, and dependency injection."]